cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a new target criterion for model confidence in deep neural networks and focuses on failure prediction. The main application area is image classification and semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical guarantees for the proposed criterion, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
